ZCZC EE14
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 062300 UTC
A COMPLEX DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS EXP TO LIE ACROSS
SCOTLAND ON MONDAY EVENING WITH ONE CENTRE 962 NEAR
SHETLAND MOV AWAY NE INTO THE NORWEGIAN SEA DURING
TUESDAY. THE OTHER CENTRE 973 NEAR THE HEBRIDES IS EXP
TO MOV S AND THEN E ACROSS NERN ENGLAND DURING TUESDAY
AND THEN INTO THE N SEA AND FILL. DURING WEDNESDAY A NEW
DPN ATLANTIC LOW WILL MOV E TO LIE JUST W OF SEA AREA
SHANNON 977 AND THEN MOV E INTO THE BRITISH ISLES
DURING THURSDAY. STRG MAINLY W WINDS OR GALES ARE EXP TO
AFFECT ALL AREAS ON MONDAY EVENING AND DURING TUESDAY
WITH SEV GALES LIKELY FOR A TIME. WINDS BECMG MAINLY NW
ON TUESDAY AND THEN EASE FOR A TIME EARLY ON WEDNESDAY
BUT FURTHER STRG S TO SW WINDS OR GALES ARE EXP TO SPREAD
ACROSS ALL AREAS LATER ON WEDNESDAY AND DURING THURSDAY
